responses.answer: Curie is a unit of radioactivity, but the unit that represents one disintegration per second is Becquerel.
Maternal mortality ratio represents the ratio of maternal deaths per 100,000 live births related to pregnancy, childbirth, and puerperium.
Chylomicrons are lipoproteins composed of triglycerides and contain the highest proportion of triglycerides.
Delayed-type (type IV) hypersensitivity is a hypersensitivity reaction driven by T cells, also known as delayed_type_hypersensitivity.
The thyroxine test using radioactive isotopes evaluates thyroid activity, which is related to diseases of the thyroid gland.
